But it should handle the SkipDir, there is a same issue, https://github.com/golang/go/issues/16280

So it changed as


err1 := walkFn(path, info, nil)
if err1 != nil {
   if err1 == filepath.SkipDir{
      return err1
   }
}
names, err := readDirNames(path)
if err != nil {
}

it will be a backwards compatible change.

The problem is it will be a large amount of memory if the directory has a large number of files.
The skipdir would not walk.

